LeConte, 1847 designated by Netolitzky (1943b: 61). Etymology. Unknown [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="431" pageNumber="432" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
Northern Hemisphere, with two species in the Nearctic (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="LeConte" baseAuthorityYear="1847" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Bembidion planatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and Palaearctic (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gebler" baseAuthorityYear="1833" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="altaicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Bembidion altaicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gebler in Asia) Regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="431" pageNumber="432" type="identification">
<paragraph pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
The North American species is treated in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lindrothâ€™s">Lindroth's</normalizedToken>
(1963b: 284) monograph.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="431" pageNumber="432" type="taxonomic note">
<paragraph pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Taxonomic Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="431" pageNumber="432">
This subgenus was placed in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Plataphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Plataphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky by Netolitzky (1943b: 61) and Lindroth (1963b: 283) but considered a valid taxon by Toledano (2008: 12). According to Maddison (2012: 569), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Melomalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Melomalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not closely related to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Plataphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="431" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="431" pageNumber="432">Plataphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
